Fixed, more or less: Putting
* {
-GtkScrollbar-has-backward-stepper: 1;
-GtkScrollbar-has-forward-stepper: 1;
}
into ~/.config/gtk-3.0/gtk.css restores the arrow buttons, and fiddling with Thunderbird's userChrome.css makes the scroll bars a sane width.

